Package com.clarionmedia.infinitum.orm.annotation

Provides the annotations which back the Infinitum ORM.

See: Description

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Column
    This annotation indicates the name of a column a Field is mapped to.
    Entity
    This annotation is used to indicate the persistence state of a model.
    ManyToMany
    This annotation indicates that the annotated Field represents a many-to-many relationship with another persistent class.
    ManyToOne
    This annotation indicates that the annotated Field represents a many-to-one relationship with another persistent class.
    NotNull
    This annotation indicates that the Field may not contain a null value when being persisted to the database because its associated column is "not null".
    OneToMany
    This annotation indicates that the annotated Field represents a one-to-many relationship with another persistent class.
    OneToOne
    This annotation indicates that the annotated Field represents a one-to-one relationship with another persistent class.
    Persistence
    This annotation is used to indicate the persistence mode of a class Field.
    PrimaryKey
    This annotation indicates if a Field is a primary key.
    Rest
    This annotation indicates the name of an endpoint field a Field is mapped to for a RESTful web service.
    Table
    This annotation indicates the name of a table an entity is mapped to.
    Unique
    This annotation indicates that the Field value must be unique to the table when being persisted to the database.

Package com.clarionmedia.infinitum.orm.annotation Description

Provides the annotations which back the Infinitum ORM. These annotations are used to provide the framework with metadata for persistent classes.
